---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={`About ${SITE.name} — what we cover and how we cite.`} pathname="/about">
  <article class="max-w-prose mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 pt-14 pb-20 prose-article">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight !mt-0">About {SITE.name}</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-[color:var(--muted)]">{SITE.tagline}</p>

    <p>
      {SITE.name} is an AI-curated news site for curious humans. Every story takes the latest from labs, papers, and the
      people building this stuff, and turns it into a clear writeup with a <strong>practical guide</strong> at the end so
      you can actually try the thing.
    </p>

    <h2>How we curate</h2>
    <p>
      We pull from official RSS feeds (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google DeepMind, Meta AI, Mistral, Hugging Face) and a small
      set of independent voices (Karpathy, Simon Willison, Jack Clark, Lilian Weng, Sebastian Raschka). We occasionally
      cite public social posts with permission and full attribution. We rewrite everything in our own voice.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial &amp; copyright policy</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Every article is <strong>rewritten</strong>, not copied. We add framing, structure, and reader-useful context.</li>
      <li>Any direct quote is <strong>≤ 25 words</strong>, in quotation marks, with an inline link to the source.</li>
      <li>Every article lists its <strong>references</strong> at the bottom — minimum one, usually two to four.</li>
      <li>If we cite a social post, we link the original and quote within the same 25-word limit.</li>
      <li>When in doubt about reuse rights, we link instead of quote.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we operate</h2>
    <p>
      An AI agent runs daily, scans the sources above, picks 1–3 stories that are high-signal for general readers, and
      drafts the writeups. A verification script blocks any draft from publishing if it lacks references, breaks
      the &lt;25-word quote rule, or omits a section. The rules live in
      <a href={`${SITE.repoUrl}/blob/main/AGENTS.md`}>AGENTS.md</a> so every run is held to the same standard.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Spotted an error or have a tip? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
